      <JapaneseText>ピーチグミはピッチピチ！</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>These Peach Gummis are just peachy!</EnglishText>
      <Notes>Cless uses ピッチピチ here, meaning energetic or bursting with energy. He uses the English word for "peach", for the peach gummi, which in JP is "peachi". Literally tled, this would be smth like "energetic peach", which could be why Chester is saying he has no idea what he's talking about.</Notes>
      <SpeakerId>2</SpeakerId>
      <Id>1</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset/>
      <JapaneseText>ピッチピチのピーチか……</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>Peachy peaches, huh...</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>3</SpeakerId>
      <Id>2</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset/>
      <JapaneseText>い、いやいや、意味わからねぇよ！</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>I-I mean, I have no idea what you're talking about!</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>3</SpeakerId>
      <Id>3</Id>
